==English==
===Phrasal Verb===
''to'' '''[[rule]] [[out]]''' ''something''
#To cross an item out by drawing a straight line through it, often by using a ruler.

''to'' '''rule out''' ''something''<BR>
''to'' '''rule''' ''something'' '''out'''
#To reject an option or possibility.
#:''As John Doe had an alibi, the police were able to '''rule''' him '''out''' as a suspect.''

====Synonyms====
*(''cross an item out''): [[cross out]], [[delete]], [[strike out]]
*(''reject an option''): [[eliminate]], [[prohibit]], [[preclude]], [[reject]]

====Antonyms====
*(''reject an option''): [[consider]], [[rule in]]